P Hit New Highs

Stocks jumped to new highs today after Morgan Stanley (MS) reported better-than-expected earnings and oil prices rose, boosting the energy sector. The Nasdaq Composite gained 0.6% to 6,385.04. Instinet's Frank Cappelleri marvels at the Nasdaq, which has rallied for a ninth consecutive day: [Through the] first 12 trading days of July, the index has experienced advances in 10 of them... As we all know, the spirited turnaround started AFTER the NDX had breached a key uptrend line, courtesy of a solidly negative second half of June.
